	<h2 style="margin-bottom:0px;">High D Performance Management</h2>
	<h1 style="text-align:center; margin-top:0px;">Strengths and Weaknesses</h1>
	<br>
	<h3 style="margin-bottom:5px;">Planning and Goal Setting</h3>
	<table class="with-border" cellpadding="3" ID="Table1">
		<tr>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Strengths</th>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Weaknesses</th>
		</tr>
		<tr valign="top">
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>Lets people know where the organization is heading (destination, the road map, their role)</li>
					<li>Sets aggressive goals</li>
					<li>Demands results and focuses on accomplishments.</li>
					<li>Clearly delineates the goal; ties to business results</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>May be too brief in explaining why these particular goals</li>
					<li>May tell rather than get employee’s input</li>
					<li>May not point out risks</li>
					<li>May present the goal only from his or her perspective</li>
					<li>May not focus on benefits to individual employee</li>
					<li>May not check to see that goals are clear</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
		</tr>
	</table>
	
	<h3 style="margin-bottom:5px;">Measuring and Monitoring Progress/Coaching</h3>
	<table class="with-border" cellpadding="3" ID="Table2">
		<tr>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Strengths</th>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Weaknesses</th>
		</tr>
		<tr valign="top">
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>Lets people know about major issues influencing the organization</li>
					<li>Lets people know what is expected</li>
					<li>Keeps people focused on the goal</li>
					<li>Focuses on issues rather than personalities</li>
					<li>Allows and encourages risk taking</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>May instill fear</li>
					<li>Makes broad, sweeping statements without backing them up</li>
					<li>Impatient when followers are slow to commit or take longer to get on board</li>
					<li>May exhibit little tolerance for feedback or opposing views</li>
					<li>May not listen well</li>
					<li>May coach in broad, sweeping statements with little about the <em>how</em></li>
				</ul>
			</td>
		</tr>
	</table>
	
	<h3 style="margin-bottom:5px;">Evaluating Performance</h3>
	<table class="with-border" cellpadding="3" ID="Table3">
		<tr>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Strengths</th>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Weaknesses</th>
		</tr>
		<tr valign="top">
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>Encourages self development</li>
					<li>Brings out the best in people</li>
					<li>Delegates responsibility and doesn’t micromanage</li>
					<li>Makes expectations clear</li>
					<li>Doesn’t fret over the small stuff</li>
					<li>Provides immediate feedback</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>Generally less concerned with developing people</li>
					<li>Expects everyone to perform as he or she would perform</li>
					<li>Focuses on problems rather than solutions</li>
					<li>Expects self motivation from everyone</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
		</tr>
	</table>
	
	<h3 style="margin-bottom:5px;">Conducting Development Review Session/Strategies</h3>
	<table class="with-border" cellpadding="3" ID="Table4">
		<tr>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Strengths</th>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Weaknesses</th>
		</tr>
		<tr valign="top">
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>Encourages self development</li>
					<li>Contagious energy and enthusiasm</li>
					<li>Exhibits confidence about ultimate success in reaching goal</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>Can be intimidating</li>
					<li>Quick to criticize and focus on negatives</li>
					<li>Tends to look forward rather than examining the past carefully for learning potential</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
		</tr>
	</table>